      "provider": "nflats",
      "price": 63,
      "description": "Cancellation Rule: Strict\nThis superb and private vintage apartment is located on the ground floor of a classic white stone house built in 1910 on the top street of the best neighborhood in Canada, the heart of Plateau Mont-Royal. Rue Marquette is a large tree-lined residential street with direct access to the expansive Lafontaine park while Mont-Royal avenue is a few steps away with all the shops, restaurants and bars. Original woodwork and plaster moldings have been preserved, 10 foot ceilings, original red pine and maple floors thru the apartment.\r\n\r\nThis charming 2.5 apartment sports huge windows providing excellent light, a comfortable water radiator heating system, a newly rebuilt  bathroom, a large closet and an amazingly comfortable Zen Body' Queen size organic bed.   Everything is included: heat, electricity, hot water cable TV and a very fast WIFI internet.  The apartment is nicely furnished with a small desk, a couch, a dining table for four, 100% cotton linen, good cooking stuff and all right amenities. \r\n\r\nThere is a 24/7 grocery store, gym and Second Cup, at the corner, next to a SAQ liquor store, fruit stores, bakeries and everything else you might need. This location is easy to commute to and from with Mont-Royal mtro station 10 minutes away and a Bixi bike rental station at the corner. If you're a bit athletic, riding a bike thru the parks, up the mountain or over the bridge to St-Helene Island is a dream. Easy access to Parc Jean-Drapeau, the Mount Royal, Old Montreal. Ideal for a couple or a single person.  Smoke and pet free environment. ",
