      "provider": "nflats",
      "price": 129,
      "description": "Cancellation Rule: Semi-flexible\nllo from Montreal!\r\n\r\nWhether you are coming for a visit or work, this flat is perfect for you! All the best attractions Montreal has to offer and are within a 10 minutes walk radius. Don't take my word for it; ask the 6 overcharging hotels surrounding this beautiful apartment.\r\n\r\nYou feel like seeing a lot of action? Walk 5 minutes towards Ste-Catherine St. and you reached the big Montreal festivals on \"Quartier des Spectacles\", Metropolis or Club Soda showing great bands every night. Keep walking on Ste-Catherine to explore the various shops and restaurants.\r\n\r\nYou feel like having a relaxed time? Walk 10 minutes towards Vieux-Port crossing Chinatown and you reached Old Montreal filled with delicious restaurants and beautiful art galleries. Take a stroll and enjoy the unique sights Vieux-Port has to offer.\r\n\r\nYou can leave your car parked in the street the whole stay.  Whether you want to walk, use the public transport or enjoy a ride on a Bixi, this location allows you to visit the city at your rhythm.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, you will sleep in the heart of the city and every commodity (grocery, barber, convenient store, florist, etc.) are also within walking distance.\r\n\r\nThe flat itself is well isolated from sound and outside temperature. AC becomes a life saver during the hot summer days!\r\n\r\nThe place comes with all amenities:\r\n\r\n-Hair Dryer\r\n-Washer & Dryer\r\n-Refrigerator\r\n-Microwave\r\n-Diswasher\r\n-Oven\r\n-AC/Heating\r\n-Wi-Fi\r\n-51\" Television*\r\n-5.1 Surround Sound System\r\n\r\n*You need a laptop with HDMI or Displayport output to watch something since I do not have cable\r\n\r\nIn brief, this place is absolutely perfect for anyone looking for a clean, affordable apartment in the heart of downtown Montreal.\r\n\r\nDo not hesitate to send me a message if you have more questions!",
