      "description": "Cancellation Rule: Semi-flexible\nLovely cottage with lots of sunshine in the afternoon and a beautiful garden in the back. Great for a group of 4 to 6 people. \r\n\r\nThe house is century old, has a lot of charm, and is in a quiet neighbourhood. There is a confortable bed (queen size) in the big room upstairs, which has a view on the garden, and small attending bathroom. Downstairs there is a small room (futon style base with queen size mattress) and a living room with a sofa-bed (queen size).\r\n\r\nIn the heart of the trendy Plateau, near Mont-Royal and Rachel street, two minutes away from Lafontaine parc, you are close to everything: cafs, bakeries, restaurants, grocery stores, shops, etc. Mont-Royal and Sherbrooke subway stations are at 15 mn walking distance or 10 minutes by bus (the 97, 45 and 29). There is a bixi (bicycle rental) station a block away.\r\n\r\nThere is a parking space behind the house for a medium size car.\r\n\r\nI love meeting people from different countries and would be delighted to tell you about places to explore. I speak french and english, some basic spanish. \r\n\r\nNon smoking house.",
