      "provider": "nflats",
      "price": 39,
      "description": "Cancellation Rule: Custom\nSmall room on the first floor in a lovely cottage with a beautiful garden. There is a confortable queen size bed (futon style base with real matress). The house is century old, has a lot of charm, and is in a quiet neighbourhood. \r\n\r\nIn the heart of the trendy Plateau, two minutes away from Lafontaine parc, near Mont-Royal and Rachel street, you are close to everything: cafs, bakeries, restaurants, grocery stores, shops, etc. There is a possibility to park a small car at the back of the house. Mont-Royal and Sherbrooke subway stations are at 15 mn walking distance or 10 minutes by bus (the 97, 45 and 29). Bixi bike station is one street away. \r\n\r\nI love meeting people from different countries and would be delighted to tell you about places to explore. I speak french and english, plus some basic spanish. \r\n\r\nI sleep in another room upstairs, but you have access to the kitchen and the garden. Sheets and towels provided. \r\n\r\nI live with my charming little boy born febuary 5th, 2013. He is very sociable and curious, rarely cries.The rooms are on separate floors and each have a door for privacy. \r\n\r\nYou have access to the kitchen and the beautiful garden. Sheets and towels provided. \r\n\r\n",
