      "description": "Cancellation Rule: Flexible\nMontral is a cosmopolitan city with tons to offer. Whether you are visiting for one of the many festivals, restaurants, or here to experience the French culture, you'll be happy staying at this large and sunny apartment in one of the hippest areas of Montreal called \"Plateau Mont Royal\". \r\n\r\nWonderful for those who have a passion for food and cooking. The fully equipped kitchen is very big, and includes a fridge, stove, oven, toaster oven, and is stacked with everything you need to entertain and cook up a storm. Off of the kitchen in the rear of the apartment is one of 2 patios and patio set to sun yourself. The dining room has 6 seats for celebrating those special meals with friends and family.\r\n\r\nThe living room is warm and inviting, with TV and DVD player, and a door leading to the front balcony. The bedroom is a good size and there is also a queen size air mattress for the living room, so the apartment can potentially sleep 4.\r\n\r\nWasher and dryer. Hair dryer. Linens, towels and sheets included.\r\n\r\nThe apartment has hardwood floors, WiFi internet, A/C in the kitchen and fans to cool you during the summer heat. \r\n\r\nThis apartment, ideally located for your stay in Montreal, is in the heart of the Plateau Mont-Royal one block from the intersection of two lively streets, Mont-Royal av and St Laurent Blvd, where you can find fabulous restos, bistros, vintage stores, bars, cafes, cheese shops, fresh bread, SAQ for buying wines and liquor, chocolatiers and more... all within seconds of the apartment.  \r\n\r\nYou'll be minutes away from St. Denis, another great street for people-watching as you enjoy a coffee or beer on one of its terraces, and 10-15 mins walking distance to Laurier, Fairmount, St-Viateur, Bernard Street, Park Avenue, and the Mountain (Mont Royal). Walk a little further and enjoy Parc LaFontaine, Little Italy, Jean Talon market, and Outremont. \r\n\r\nMount Royal metro station on the Orange line is 8 blocks away that takes you to Old-Montreal in 7 minutes, McGill and other parts of Downtown in 6-12 minutes, the June Grandprix F1 racing track in 10 minutes. Rosemont Metro is also very close, as is St-Hubert Plaza shopping complex with its glass canopy. \r\n\r\nThere are also buses on St-Laurent and St-Urbain and several Bixi stands within a two-block radius.\r\n\r\nThe airport is a 20-40 minute cab ride away, depending on traffic. \r\n\r\nStreet parking available.",
